 So they have placed this word dharma as an alternative for the religion.

102
00:07:52 --> 00:07:56
 Hinduism instead of Hindu matam, they call it as sanatana dharma.

103
00:07:56 --> 00:08:02
 So when Krishna told swadharma, nidramasriya, means if you are born as Hindu,

104
00:08:02 --> 00:08:07
 be as a Hindu and die nidramasriya, die as a Hindu.

105
00:08:07 --> 00:08:10
 There is no need of changing the religion.

106
00:08:10 --> 00:08:14
 You did not become a Christian, you did not become Muslim.

107
00:08:14 --> 00:08:20
 Because all these religions are leading to same God.

108
00:08:20 --> 00:08:26
 So different religions were created and God came to different religions in different forms.

109
00:08:26 --> 00:08:33
 The same God came in different forms and preached the same syllabus.

110
00:08:33 --> 00:08:39
 You see any religion the main syllabus contains three main items.

111
00:08:39 --> 00:08:45
 One is God, another is heaven, another is hell.

112
00:08:45 --> 00:08:49
 God for spiritual side, for personal worship, to get the grace of God.

113
00:08:49 --> 00:08:51
 That is for nivrutti.

114
00:08:51 --> 00:08:58
 And for pravrutti where dharma, justice is to be protected and injustice to be condemned,

115
00:08:58 --> 00:09:01
 for that swaga and naraka, heaven and hell are.

116
00:09:01 --> 00:09:04
 Heaven and hell constitute pravrutti.

117
00:09:04 --> 00:09:08
 God constitutes nivrutti. Of course God is also present in pravrutti.

118
00:09:08 --> 00:09:11
 He is the support of everything, whole thing.

119
00:09:11 --> 00:09:15
