158
00:12:14 --> 00:12:18
 If you do good deeds, rewards are given through heaven.

159
00:12:18 --> 00:12:22
 If you do bad deeds, punishments are given through hell.

160
00:12:22 --> 00:12:24
 So everything is same.

161
00:12:24 --> 00:12:25
 Set up is same.

162
00:12:25 --> 00:12:28
 Infrastructure is same in every religion.

163
00:12:28 --> 00:12:32
 So there is no need of changing your religion.

164
00:12:32 --> 00:12:36
 Of course there may be some defects and some merits.

165
00:12:36 --> 00:12:39
 Some defects are present in every religion.

166
00:12:39 --> 00:12:44
 Some type of defects may be in Hinduism, some other types of defects may be in other religion.

167
00:12:44 --> 00:12:48
 Or sometimes same defects also may be present there.

168
00:12:48 --> 00:12:54
 So avoid the defects of religion by your sharp analysis.

169
00:12:54 --> 00:12:57
 In any religion you will face merits and defects.

170
00:12:57 --> 00:13:03
